Which statement correctly describes what this method does (assuming `data` contains only strings of length at least 2)?

```java
import java.util.*;

public class EasterSort {
    public static void applyBasketOwnerOrder(List<String> data) {
        data.sort(new Comparator<String>() {
            @Override
            public int compare(String a, String b) {
                if (a.charAt(1) != b.charAt(1)) {
                    return a.charAt(1) - b.charAt(1);
                } else {
                    return a.charAt(0) - b.charAt(0);
                }
            }
        });
    }
}
```

Which statement about this use of `parallelStream()` is correct (assuming this program is executed multiple times)?

```java
import java.util.*;

public class ParallelEggIDs {
    public static void printEggIDs() {
        List<Integer> numbers = Arrays.asList(5, 3, 2, 4, 1);

        numbers.parallelStream()
               .forEach(n -> System.out.print(n + " "));
    }
}
```

For `isGuestAllowed(GuestType.UNKNOWN)`, the returned result is `false`. Which statement correctly explains why this happens?

```java
public enum GuestType {
    FRIEND, FAMILY, UNKNOWN;
}

public class EasterParty {

    public static boolean isGuestAllowed(GuestType guestType) {
        if (guestType == GuestType.UNKNOWN) {
            return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```
